I know people don’t respond to long thought out comments but I’m gonna do it anyways.

@ why did they spend money on a clown?

For starters when businesses go out of business they normally squeeze as much money out of it as possible so they hired Arthur to get people to go into the store.

Also the reason the joker runs after those kids is b/c the sign has a financial value so if it’s broken the business (that has lost its source of income) would sue the company they went to , to hire Arthur so it’s not that unrealistic that Arthur would chase them.

Edit : @ for some reason you’re acting like kids being awful to someone especially in a city in Gotham is somehow inconceivable.

Edit 2 : @ Arthur has PBA so he goes into uncontrollable fits of laughter............. so that’s why he’s “cry laughing”.

Edit 3 : @ you sin the movie b/c the clocks have @ on them but acknowledge later that a clock has @ on it ........ also the reason the clocks have @ on them is b/c when clocks are being sold it’s supposed to mirror a smile.(Plus 2 sins one for inconsistency and another for the @ = Smiles part)

Edit 4 : @ yes , actually that is how it works which is why when he stops taking the medication he starts to unravel and murder people.

Edit 5 : @ ummm how is it the movies fault the stairs became a tourist attraction?

Edit 6 : @ mentioning the fact Arthur’s mom worked for Thomas Wayne isn’t a Batman reference .

Edit 7 : @ Joker and King of Comedy share several concepts , you probably called it a remake b/c that’s the thing you normally say about Joker to critique it but there’s so many differences between these movies the comment you made almost implies you never watched King of Comedy.

Edit 8 : @ yeah that’s b/c it’s supposed to show how delusional Arthur really is.

Edit 9 : @ yes Arthur accepts the gun from a guy who makes fun of him b/c Arthur was attacked and he needs something to defend himself with.

Edit 10 : @ Gotham is a place filled with scummy people you think his boss would care that he was beat up?

Edit 11 : @ Staircase to He......... what’re you talking about you acknowledged the stairs were real earlier when you gave it 10 sins for .... actually no good reason.

Edit 12 : @ Don’t worry Jeremy we knew you were biased b/c of all the nit picking and mental gymnastics in this “review” 😁.

Edit 13 : @ OMG THE HOSPITAL HIRED A CLOWN TO CHEER DYING CHILDREN UP............. imagine my surprise.

Edit 14 : @ Yes the Hospital had Arthur removed b/c of the gun so once he’s by himself he calls his boss from a pay phone........... it’s most likely dark b/c Arthur was probably questioned by the police as to where he got the gun from and why he had it which could’ve taken a long time to do.

Edit 15 : @ Wow it’s almost like Arthur is going through small coincidental situations that are ruining his life little by little until he can’t contain his emotions anymore and he starts harming those around him.

Edit 16 : @ Arthur Isn’t supposed to be a sympathetic character they show him being screwed over but the movie doesn’t treat him like a sympathetic character at all.

Edit 17 : @ he does become the Joker but he inspired the Joker who constantly fights against Batman.......... you know b/c there’s multiple Jokers.

Edit 18 : @ So you based this sin of a feeling without you actually knowing if it’s true......... you just summed up this review.

Edit 19 : @ d-do you not know what adrenaline is?

Edit 20 : @ yeah I get that you like Scorsese but Endgame is Cinema it’s its own art form but I’m not going to count this b/c this is based on our own objective view of what Cinema is.

Edit 21: @:Joker earned those nominations don’t be spiteful.

Edit 22 : @ Almost like Arthur is an “unreliable narrator” b/c of his descent into madness.

Edit 23 : @ having a staircase in your movie isn’t a sin.......... there stairs.

Edit 24 : @ b/c a poor guy (don’t tell me you think a clown is rich) killed three upcoming business men in cold blood ........... it’s called “connecting dots” b/c they weren’t there they’re speculating on what happened.

Edit 25 : @ OMG HE ACTUALLY FOUND AN ACTUAL REFERENCE THE MOVIE MADE ABOUT BATMAN!!!!!

Edit 27 : @ b/c she’s also delusional.

Edit 28 : @ well iPhones weren’t around so when men went to work they read the good ol paper............also b/c they probably heard about the killer clown and wanted more info.

Edit 29 : @ the movie about the Joker has Batman references in it ........... OMG😱😱😱😱.

Edit 30 : @ People bringing cameras to a comedy club aren’t uncommon and Murray is a big celebrity do the math ....... oh you won’t

People who work for Murray (a comedian/late night show host) most likely go to comedy clubs to record people to provide entertainment to the audience and they show Arthur’s bit just b/c it was really weird.

snippet.textDisplay:
11:50 Cringy for a white guy to call a black guy brother?
I disagree, I am homeless and white but I still call all the other homeless guys brother, white or black it dont matter because they call me brother too. Because a lot of us see past that race stuff on the streets and in shelters because we actually got real problems to worry about like survival so we help eachother out for the most part. I show kindness and people treat me the same. Homeless people with or without mental health and addiction problems make up the majority. But I tell you this they have given and done more for me then any wealthy or well off family have ever done for me. And I do the same for them. We are still human and I think people forget that.
This movie was hard to watch but it's a f***ing good thing because mental illness is treated as taboo and misunderstood even by the doctors and professional's that work in the field. I know first hand, and in no way am I saying having mental illness means your free to commit crime or murder. But I am saying that mental illnesses can cripple and affect people in ways that are way beyond anyone's control. And we do not fully understand it but I know firsthand what its like to not have control of your life and be possessed by something that causes you to act or do things in a way that you do not choose to do willingly.
Only the ones with the affliction understand and many educated mental health professionals think they know best but only fools think themselves wise in things they havent experienced or fully understood yet and they are often the ones that cause the most harm to people with the chronic disorders and relapses. The more severe an illness is the more it's falsely understood and the person's options for treatment are neglected to only medication alone and that's not a Solution.
Love others as you love yourself. And do more for others instead of doing more for yourself. If a homeless drug addict with mental illness can do this then how can others who actually have a home not do the same or atleast treat those with less than with dignity and love because no one is better then each other we are all human.

I should add as someone who lives in a disadvantaged place with high unemployment. One never complains about their job and definitely never admits to something resulting in lost revenue. There are plenty of people to replace you. Seems obvious to me but I guess if you're lucky enough and privileged enough you don't see it. And sabotage can lead to less work so you suck everything up and pretend it's ok.

Really liked this movie, but yeah, the joker is definitely an idiot. Not sure how he goes on to be the crazed genius, you need to be some kind of genius, genius to begin with before you become the crazed one. and nothing in this movie reveals any hint of higher intelligence, or average for that matter.
